Histograms

Haley Jeppson

2019-06-24

Source: vignettes/example-gallery-06-histograms.Rmd
example-gallery-06-histograms.Rmd

This document is adapted from the Bar Charts section of the Altair Example Gallery.

Our first step is to set up our environment:

# devtools::install_github("vegawidget/altair")
library("altair")
library("tibble")
library("tidyr")

vega_data <- import_vega_data()

Histogram with a Global Mean Overlay

Altair example

Data

#glimpse(vega_data$movies())

Chart

data <- vega_data$movies$url

bar <- 
  alt$Chart(data)$
  mark_bar()$
  encode(
    x = alt$X("IMDB_Rating:Q", bin=TRUE, axis=NULL),
    y = alt$Y("count()")
  )

rule <- 
  alt$Chart(data)$
  mark_rule(color = "red")$
  encode(
    x = "mean(IMDB_Rating):Q",
    size = alt$value(5)
  )

chart <- (bar + rule)

chart

Layered Histogram

Altair example

Data

Definition

data <- 
  data_frame(
    Trial_A = rnorm(1000, 0, 0.8),
    Trial_B = rnorm(1000, -2, 1),
    Trial_C = rnorm(1000, 3, 2)
  ) %>%
  gather(Experiment, Measurement)
#> Warning: `data_frame()` is deprecated, use `tibble()`.
#> This warning is displayed once per session.
glimpse(data)
#> Observations: 3,000
#> Variables: 2
#> $ Experiment  <chr> "Trial_A", "Trial_A", "Trial_A", "Trial_A", "Trial_Aâ€¦
#> $ Measurement <dbl> -0.83612939, -1.04936681, -1.32880685, 0.52459873, -â€¦

Chart

chart <- 
  alt$Chart(data)$
  mark_area(opacity = 0.3, interpolate="step")$
  encode(
    x = alt$X("Measurement", bin = alt$Bin(maxbins = 100)),
    y = alt$Y("count()", stack = NULL),
    color = alt$Color("Experiment")
  )

chart

chart <- 
  alt$Chart(vega_data$cars())$
  mark_bar()$
  encode(
    x = alt$X("Horsepower:Q", bin = TRUE),
    y = "count(Horsepower)",
    row = "Origin"
  )
